<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,310,1221,1247]" box="[189,310,1221,1247]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1221,1247]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1221,1247]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,1399,1268,1435]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
This species differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Remm" authorityYear="1974" box="[492,652,1268,1294]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pachypyga">
<emphasis box="[492,652,1268,1294]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">B. pachypyga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having yellowish legs with indistinct dark brown bands and femora with 2–3 spines. Male gonocoxite simple, without any process (
<figureCitation box="[1015,1106,1303,1329]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[320,1270,267,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[307,1280,245,1867]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 3. Bezzia (Sivabezzia) spp. A–D. Bezzia pachypyga, ♂ (from Remm 1974). A. Genitalia, ♂. B. Parameres. C. Aedeagus. D. Seminal capsules, ♀. – E–I. Bezzia melanoflava (from Clastrier 1958). E. Genitalia, ♂. F. Parameres. G. Aedeagus, ventral view. H. Aedeagus, lateral view. I. Seminal capsules, ♀." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3827457" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3827457/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
); parameres slender, rodlike; aedeagus short, with low basal arch, and dorsal, submedian processes shorter than parameres (
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[320,1270,267,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[307,1280,245,1867]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 3. Bezzia (Sivabezzia) spp. A–D. Bezzia pachypyga, ♂ (from Remm 1974). A. Genitalia, ♂. B. Parameres. C. Aedeagus. D. Seminal capsules, ♀. – E–I. Bezzia melanoflava (from Clastrier 1958). E. Genitalia, ♂. F. Parameres. G. Aedeagus, ventral view. H. Aedeagus, lateral view. I. Seminal capsules, ♀." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3827457" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3827457/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
F–H) (
<bibRefCitation author="Clastrier J." box="[281,454,1373,1400]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="192 - 258" refId="ref13828" refString="Clastrier J. 1958. Notes sur les Ceratopogonides. IV. Ceratopogonides d'Afrique Occidentale francaise. Archives de l'Institut Pasteur d'Algerie 36: 192 - 258." type="journal article" year="1958">Clastrier 1958</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Boorman J. &amp; van Harten A." box="[467,818,1374,1400]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="427 - 462" refId="ref13709" refString="Boorman J. &amp; van Harten A. 2002. Some Ceratopogonidae (Insecta: Diptera) from the Arabian Peninsula, with particular reference to the Republic of Yemen. Fauna of Arabia 19: 427 - 462." type="journal article" year="2002">Boorman &amp; van Harten 2002</bibRefCitation>
). Female with 2 conical seminal capsules, widest on middle portion, with long necks (
<figureCitation box="[616,698,1409,1435]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[320,1270,267,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[307,1280,245,1867]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 3. Bezzia (Sivabezzia) spp. A–D. Bezzia pachypyga, ♂ (from Remm 1974). A. Genitalia, ♂. B. Parameres. C. Aedeagus. D. Seminal capsules, ♀. – E–I. Bezzia melanoflava (from Clastrier 1958). E. Genitalia, ♂. F. Parameres. G. Aedeagus, ventral view. H. Aedeagus, lateral view. I. Seminal capsules, ♀." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3827457" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3827457/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 3I</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
